I was ripped about the loot rules being changed after the loot had dropped, when we had done the raid under a different set of rules.  I like rules, I don't always agree with them, which is why I tried to convince Cheatch to change them before going in, but once they were set in place, I expect them to be followed.  Good or bad, when rules are set and people go ahead operating under said rules it's not fair to anyone to change the rules after the raid is over and loot is dropped.  I like things neat and tidy.  I like to know when someone says we are doing something a certain way, we are, period.  It's why I love raiding and being a member of FE.  I may not always like the rules and policies, but I can count on the officers and leaders sticking to them in all situations without fail.<br>
<br>
So, in a nutshell, that's my gripe.  You don't form a raid, insist on one set of rules, and after all is said and done, arbitrarily change them. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://groups.msn.com/_Secure/0MwDcAoASbuI7OZ5yIceHaP39Dwigymrw7YcJinaML1euPtuElY352BHSRnfdaGxIsA33DsXknCipg2THJfvTtg/tenabrielcopy.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
